---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About | Mahdi Khan"
  description="Hi, I'm Mahdi Khan. I write practitioner-grade analysis on AI agents and multi-agent systems."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-10 block">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-color)] mb-4">About Me</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[var(--text-muted)]">
        Decoding the reality of AI agents from the hype.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-container prose-content">
      <p>
        Hi, I'm Mahdi Khan. I'm a software engineer and technical leader focused on the architecture, orchestration, and practical deployment of AI agents.
      </p>
      
      <h2>What this site is about</h2>
      <p>
        The AI landscape is moving at breakneck speed. Every week there's a new 
        framework, a new paper, or a new "AGI is here" thread on X. For practitioners 
        actually trying to build reliable systems, the signal-to-noise ratio is terrible.
      </p>
      <p>
        I built this platform to be the resource I wished existed: <strong>practitioner-grade analysis</strong> 
        that goes deeper than a 280-character hot take, but is more accessible and applied than an academic paper.
      </p>
      
      <h3>What you'll find here:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Weekly Digests:</strong> Synthesis of the 5-8 things that actually matter each week.</li>
        <li><strong>Deep Dives:</strong> Architectural breakdowns of frameworks like LangGraph, CrewAI, and AutoGPT.</li>
        <li><strong>Tutorials:</strong> Step-by-step implementation guides with production-ready code.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>My Background</h2>
      <p>
        I have spent my career building scalable backend systems and, more recently, 
        taming the chaos of LLMs in production. I believe multi-agent systems represent 
        the next major paradigm shift in software architecture—moving from deterministic 
        pipelines to probabilistic, goal-oriented networks.
      </p>

      <h2>Connect</h2>
      <p>
        The best way to stay in touch is to <a href="/newsletter">subscribe to the newsletter</a>. 
        You can also find me on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://twitter.com/mahdikhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">X (Twitter)</a> for real-time thoughts</li>
        <li><a href="https://linkedin.com/in/mahdikhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a> for professional updates</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/mahdikhan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> for code and experiments</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
